- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper deals with games and their properties, specifically inheritance of convexity. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper involves graph theory and combinatorics in the form of minimum partitions and connected components. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses algorithms for computing minimum partitions and deciding inheritance of convexity. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The concept of convexity is often used in optimization problems, which are relevant to AI. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper involves communication graphs and their weights, which are related to information theory.
